
  Name:  wctomb
  
  #include <stdlib.h>
  int wctomb(char *out, wchar_t in);

  The wctomb( ) function converts the wide character in in into its
  multibyte equivalent and puts the result in the object pointed to 
  by out. The array pointed to by out must be at least MB_CUR_MAX
  characters long.

  Related Functions:  wcstombs and mbtowc

